                        <h3 class="m-y-0" style="color: #E0C023;">Rules</h3>
                        <p></p>
                        <p><ul><li> All contests begin at the designated start time of the contest on the designated start date of the contest, as displayed during contest registration. All games end at the designated end time on the designated end date of the contest as displayed during contest registration.<strong> PLEASE ENSURE YOU ARE AWARE OF THESE TERMS DURING REGISTRATION. </strong></li>
<li>  During the competition you have the ability to make decisions that demonstrate your ability as a trader. Simply put, you can buy or sell any amount of any instrument in a competition up to your available notional at any time. All actions taken are simulated. </li>
<li>  At the conclusion of the contest, your PnL, as determined by the simulated trades you took during the competition, will be graded against other participants PnL generated in the same fashion, during the specific competition all participants registered in.</li>
<li>Cash prizes are awarded based on how your PnL ranks at the end of the competition relative to the other competitors in your competition. Not the performance of any instrument or your fictional PnL.</li></ul>

                        </p>
                     </div>
