                        <p></p>
                        <h5 class="m-y-0" style="color: #E0C023;"> How do I know I'm not playing against ZeroSum employees who can see all the 'data'?</h5>
                        <p>First all users have access to the same data, we don’t know anything special!
More importantly, Employees and Directors (and their family members) of ZeroSum Gaming, LLC. are not allowed to participate in public paid contests, under any circumstances. So feel assured that you are competing against other real users!
</p>
                     </div>

  <div class="col-sm-12 m-b-md">
                        <h5 class="m-y-0" style="color: #E0C023;">Is ZeroSum regulated by a financial regulatory authority, or by the state or federal government?</h5>
                        <p>ZeroSum is a contest of skill, much like eSports or a chess tournament only here we test your trading aptitude. It is not a security or security based swap, it is a skill based contest. ZeroSum is not currently regulated by the federal government, any state government, or financial regulatory authority. Keep in mind, you do not own or actually trade any legal security instrument nor are you tied to the performance of that instrument to determine your payout. 
